Part 1: Coding Etiquette & Excel Reporting¶

This script includes the following points:¶

1. Import Data¶

2. Address PII data¶

3. Create a regional segmentation of the data¶

4. Create an exclusion flag for low-activity customers¶

5. Customer Profiling: department, age, income, number of dependants¶

6. Visualization of Customer Profiles¶

7. Aggregate the max, mean, and min variables on a customer-profile level for usage frequency and expenditure.¶

8. Compare Customer Profiles with Regions and Departments¶

9. Export Data Set¶

The following columns include PII data. They are not needed for this report, so they can be removed:

  • first_name
  • surname

Additionally, the following columns will not be used for reporting so can also be removed:

  • aisle_id
  • add_to_cart_order
  • date_joined
  • _merge

4. Create an exclusion flag for low-activity customers¶

In [20]:
#low-activity customer < 5 orders
ords_prods_cust_clean.loc[ords_prods_cust_clean['max_order']< 5, "customer_activity"] = "Low-Activity Customer"
In [21]:
#high-activity customer >= 5 orders
ords_prods_cust_clean.loc[ords_prods_cust_clean['max_order']>= 5, "customer_activity"] = "High-Activity Customer"
In [22]:
#check outputs

Group by Region¶

Customer Profile¶
In [91]:
#Group by customer profile and region
profile_region=ords_prods_cust_dept.groupby(['customer_profile','region']).size().unstack()
In [92]:
#Sort
profile_region = profile_region.loc[profile_region.sum(axis=1).sort_values(ascending = True).index]
In [93]:
#create bar graph
bar_profile_region = profile_region.plot.barh(stacked = True, title = 'Customer Profile by Region', xlabel = 'number of customers (in 100,000)')
plt.tight_layout()

The demographic information suggests classifications in the areas of income, age, and dependants. Combining these together creates 18 different customer profiles.

Mid-Income, Young Adults with Dependants are the largest group among customers. The largest customer profiles all have dependents. Mid-Income makes up 3/5 of the top customer profiles.

Across all customers profiles, the proportions of customers are the same. This means there are no regional differences in customer income, age, and number of dependants.
